## App background (concise)

Primary flows: authentication and onboarding; home feed and map exploration; multi-step spot creation and upload; search across users/places/vibes; profile and follow-request flows; deep-link routing for spot detail and subscription return.

## Architecture (concise)

- **UI** — `Spot/Views`: SwiftUI components and feature screens.
- **State** — `Spot/ViewModels`: `ObservableObject` view models.
- **Data** — `Spot/Services`, `Spot/Models`: **Supabase**-backed repositories and models; **Firebase** for analytics, Crashlytics, App Check (see `AppDelegate`).
- **Cross-cutting** — `Spot/Utils`, `Spot/Managers`: logging, validation, geohash, permissions, location, moderation policy, tours.

Global **`@EnvironmentObject`** for auth, deep links, permissions; per-screen **`@StateObject`** view models where used.

## Core module map

- **`Spot/SpotApp.swift`** — `@main`, launch orchestration, DI.
- **`Spot/AppDelegate.swift`** — Firebase, analytics/crash, app-check, URL/user-activity bridge.
- **`Spot/Views/RootView.swift`** — auth gate, tabs, deep-link/paywall overlays.
- **`Spot/Views/Components/BottomTabNavigationView.swift`** — tab shell (Home, Map, Post, Search, Profile).
- **Auth / onboarding** — `Spot/Views/Auth`, `Spot/Views/Onboarding`, `Spot/Services/Auth*`.
- **Feed** — `Spot/Views/Home`, `Spot/ViewModels/FeedViewModel.swift`, `Spot/Services/Feed/*` — `get_home_feed_v1` RPC + signing.
- **Post** — `Spot/Views/PostFlow`, `Spot/ViewModels/PostFlowViewModel.swift`, `Spot/Services/Spots/*`, `Spot/Services/Supabase/*` (publish + media).
- **Search** — `Spot/Views/Search`, `Spot/ViewModels/SearchViewModel.swift`, `Spot/Services/Search/*`.
- **Profile** — `Spot/Views/Profile`, `Spot/ViewModels/ProfileViewModel.swift`, profile/follow services.
- **Map** — `Spot/Views/Home/MapView.swift`, `Spot/ViewModels/MapViewModel.swift`, `Spot/Services/Map/*`.

## Data / service highlights

- **`Spot/Services/AuthService.swift`** — Supabase Auth + `public.users` lifecycle.
- **`Spot/Services/Feed/FeedRepository.swift`** — home feed via `get_home_feed_v1` + image signing.
- **`Spot/Services/Feed/FeedRanker.swift`** — on-device scoring (tests / experiments).
- **`Spot/Services/Supabase/SpotSupabaseRepository.swift`** — spots, media, RPCs (e.g. publish with approved assets).
- **`Spot/Services/AuthorPrivacyCache.swift`** — actor-based privacy/follow cache.
- **`Spot/Services/DeepLinkRouter.swift`**, **`Spot/ViewModels/DeepLinkState.swift`** — Universal Links and custom scheme routing.

## External integrations

- **Supabase** — Auth, Postgres, Storage for app data.
- **Firebase** — Analytics, Crashlytics, App Check only (not the data plane). See `docs/engineering/data-plane.md`.
- **Apple** — SwiftUI, MapKit, CoreLocation, UserNotifications, StoreKit, Security, PhotosUI.
- **Subscriptions** — StoreKit + hosted checkout / deep-link return (`spotapp://subscription/return`).

## Major runtime flows

1. Launch → auth gate (`WelcomeView`, `ConfirmEmailView`, or tab shell).
2. Authenticated users → tab navigation and feature VMs.
3. Feed → `get_home_feed_v1` → signing → UI.
4. Post → capture → moderation-gated media → publish RPC.
5. Search → debounced query, filters, pagination.
6. Deep links → `DeepLinkRouter` + `DeepLinkState` with auth-aware pending routes.

## Build and test commands

Use an available **iPhone Simulator** UDID (or `platform=iOS Simulator,name=…`). Prefer `xcbeautify` when installed.

```sh
SIM_ID=$(xcrun simctl list devices available | grep "iPhone" | head -n 1 | sed -E 's/.*\(([0-9A-F-]+)\).*/\1/')
BEAUTIFY=$(command -v xcbeautify >/dev/null && echo "xcbeautify" || echo "cat")

xcodebuild -scheme Spot -destination "id=$SIM_ID" build | $BEAUTIFY
xcodebuild -scheme Spot -destination "id=$SIM_ID" test | $BEAUTIFY
xcodebuild -scheme SpotTests -destination "id=$SIM_ID" test | $BEAUTIFY
xcodebuild -scheme SpotUITests -destination "id=$SIM_ID" test | $BEAUTIFY
```

Optional: `-enableCodeCoverage YES` on `xcodebuild test` when collecting coverage.

## Code coverage expectations

For new production code, aim for **meaningful** tests: happy path, empty/error branches, and guard rules. Keep test-only production changes minimal and DEBUG- or test-gated when they must exist.

Agents should run the **relevant scheme(s)** after substantive non-doc changes.
